  "ciliary_role": "Epidermal growth factor receptor pathway substrate 8 (Eps8, 8404850) is an evolutio rily conserved sig l transducer endowed with multiple functions in the control of actin dy mics and in the integration of these events with other receptor-activated sig ling functions. Depending on its association with other sig l transducers, Eps8 can regulate the activation of the Rac GTPase, a master regulator of actin remodeling (10499589 , 11524436). Eps8 knockout mice are deaf and the normal physiological development of IHCs is prevented(21526224).",
